The error `Uncaught SyntaxError: Illegal return statement` typically occurs when the JavaScript engine encounters a `return` statement outside of a function body. In a React project, this most often happens when a file is empty or contains invalid top-level code (like a `return` statement hanging in the global scope) because it was created as a placeholder but not correctly implemented.

I have identified the potential culprits—files that were previously empty or placeholders—and I am updating them with valid, minimal React component structures or proper exports. This will resolve the syntax error and allow your application to load.

