I will redesign the Ticket Item row to prioritize safety and usability.

**The Solution: "Expandable Rows" & "Smart Minus Button"**

1.  **Remove the Dangerous Trash Button:** The standalone trash button on the far right (which causes accidental clicks) will be removed completely.
2.  **Smart Minus Button:**
    *   When Quantity > 1: It acts as a standard Minus button.
    *   When Quantity = 1: It transforms into a **Red Trash Icon**. This effectively moves the "Delete" action to a predictable location (decreasing quantity to zero).
3.  **Expandable Row (Safety Valve):**
    *   Clicking the **Item Name** will now expand the row to reveal a dedicated **"Remove Item"** button.
    *   This provides a safe, intentional way to delete items with large quantities (e.g., deleting a line with 50 items without hitting minus 50 times) and prevents accidental deletion during normal scrolling.

