I have identified the cause of the "sometimes have to multi-touch" issue. It's a common UX problem where the **press animation shrinks the button's hit area**.

When you tap a button that has `active:scale-95`, the button physically shrinks under your finger. If your finger is on the edge of the button, the button might shrink *away* from your touch. When you lift your finger (`pointerup`), the browser sees you are no longer touching the element (because it shrank), so it cancels the `click` event. This makes it feel like the app ignored your tap.

**The Fix:**
I am refactoring the item tiles so the **button container remains full size** (stationary), while only the **internal content** shrinks for the visual effect. This guarantees the click registers every time, even if you tap the very edge.

I'm also adding `type="button"` to all interactive elements to prevent any default browser form behaviors.

