I've identified the specific cause of the "black screen" glitch.

The issue stems from a specific CSS performance optimization class called `content-visibility-auto` that was applied to the item grid container.

**The Technical Details:**
`content-visibility: auto` tells the browser *not* to render the content until it is strictly visible on screen. When we use the "Keep Alive" navigation (switching `display: none` to `display: flex`), the browser sometimes gets confused. It thinks the content is still "hidden" or has zero dimensions during the switch, so it simply renders nothing (black/blank space) to save resources. "Touching somewhere" fires a scroll/touch event, which wakes up the browser's layout engine to repaint the area.

I am removing this property. The "Keep Alive" architecture itself is efficient enough that we don't need this aggressive CSS optimization anymore.

