I've identified the specific CSS property causing the grid glitches (often appearing as a blank or black screen when switching tabs).

The class `content-visibility-auto` was intended to improve performance by skipping rendering for off-screen content. However, in a "Keep Alive" architecture where screens are hidden/shown using `display: none`, this optimization confuses the browser, leading it to render nothing until a scroll event forces a repaint.

I am removing this class to ensure the grid renders instantly and reliably every time you switch screens.

